    <p class="faq-sub">Quick answers to the most common questions about this topic.</p>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can I migrate from Tally to cloud without losing past years of data?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. A proper Tally migration exports every voucher, ledger, stock item and bill-wise breakup using Tally's XML or ODBC interface, then maps each record into the destination schema. Done correctly, you keep 100% of the audit trail back to your earliest Tally year.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How long does a Tally to cloud migration usually take?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">For a typical SMB with 5-10 years of Tally data and 50,000-2,00,000 vouchers, migration takes 4-6 weeks: 1 week for data audit and mapping, 2 weeks for ETL and reconciliation, 2 weeks for parallel run, and a weekend cutover.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What about my Tally TDLs and customisations?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">TDL customisations do not migrate as code, but their behaviour can be re-implemented as configuration, custom fields, or rules in the cloud platform. Most TDLs in Indian SMBs are voucher-class extensions or print formats — both are routine to recreate.</div>
    </details>
